<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11865] Auto-connection close on idle channel can race with TransportClientFactory.createClient()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11865</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The recent code added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11252&quot; title=&quot;ShuffleClient should release connection after fetching blocks had been completed in yarn&amp;#39;s external shuffle&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-11252&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-11252&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a race, where an idle channel might be closed after it&apos;s returned from a &lt;tt&gt;TransportClientFactory.createClient()&lt;/tt&gt; call, which would cause applications to see failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TransportClientFactory.createClient()&lt;/tt&gt; should reset the channel&apos;s timeout and ensure that the channel it&apos;s returning hasn&apos;t timed out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
